    {
      "id": "PopularPost95911",
      "post_content": "What if you just tear it in half, tape it back together after the game, put it back in the sleeve, and each time you play just remove the tape to take the pieces apart again? They really should've specified a minimum number of pieces.  \n  \nBut if you're just playing with friends and you want to stay true to the spirit of this without making each other waste money for no reason, I'd suggest something like only being able to use it once every 5 games, or houseruling a drawback like losing 5 life.",
      "posted_by": "achilleselbow",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost95911\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_post\">What if you just tear it in half, tape it back together after the game, put it back in the sleeve, and each time you play just remove the tape to take the pieces apart again? They really should've specified a minimum number of pieces.<br/><br/>But if you're just playing with friends and you want to stay true to the spirit of this without making each other waste money for no reason, I'd suggest something like only being able to use it once every 5 games, or houseruling a drawback like losing 5 life.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '95911'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy31177\">achilleselbow</span>\r\n                                (8/16/2010 1:42:03 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": "PopularPost111318",
      "post_content": "Instead of using [March of the Machines](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=March of the Machines) you could use [Tezzeret the Seeker](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tezzeret the Seeker), or instead of [Blacker Lotus](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blacker Lotus) you could use [Chaos Confetti](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Chaos Confetti). Or throw in all four with [Mater of Etherium](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mater of Etherium) for maximum redundancy. I thought of a deck like this, but with [Shapesharer](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shapesharer), [Imagecrafter](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Imagecrafter) and red creature stealing spells like [Act of Treason](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Act of Treason). And the win condition is simple, your opponent concedes when he realizes his [Baneslayer Angel](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Baneslayer Angel) isn't worth a game of casual magic. They say you can concede at any time and even if tearing the card to pieces is a cost, I don't think conceding uses the stack.",
      "posted_by": "venerableloki",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost111318\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl09_post\">Instead of using <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"March of the Machines\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=March of the Machines\">March of the Machines</a> you could use <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Tezzeret the Seeker\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tezzeret the Seeker\">Tezzeret the Seeker</a>, or instead of <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Blacker Lotus\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blacker Lotus\">Blacker Lotus</a> you could use <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Chaos Confetti\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Chaos Confetti\">Chaos Confetti</a>. Or throw in all four with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mater of Etherium\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mater of Etherium\">Mater of Etherium</a> for maximum redundancy. I thought of a deck like this, but with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Shapesharer\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shapesharer\">Shapesharer</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Imagecrafter\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Imagecrafter\">Imagecrafter</a> and red creature stealing spells like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Act of Treason\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Act of Treason\">Act of Treason</a>. And the win condition is simple, your opponent concedes when he realizes his <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Baneslayer Angel\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Baneslayer Angel\">Baneslayer Angel</a> isn't worth a game of casual magic. They say you can concede at any time and even if tearing the card to pieces is a cost, I don't think conceding uses the stack.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl09_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl09_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '111318'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy45566\">venerableloki</span>\r\n                                (10/21/2010 3:09:47 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl09_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>"
